		<td><b>Re: Critique this screen/these graphics</b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Thanks! I haven't mastered it, but grays have a tendency to melt since it contains a litle bit of each. White can come off as too strong, but dotting and lining darker grayscale pixels here and there can give that multicolour expression and be semi-controllable depending on what you put or don't put close to it and in what direction. It's currently just 0d 00 2d 31 in that palette but i see lots of greens in the same attribute cells, and something almost bleak pink-yellowish. This is a PAL system so i wonder what it would be like on a NTSC.<br /><br />Hah you're right - i've grown so used to it i didn't even notice. Will update the OP with a 4:3 one instad.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


